1
00:00:01,835 --> 00:00:04,129
[theme music plays]

2
00:01:26,670 --> 00:01:28,839
L, I want to meet you.

3
00:01:29,715 --> 00:01:30,716
Daikoku Wharf,

4
00:01:31,008 --> 00:01:32,843
an abandoned warehouse
known as the Yellow Box.

5
00:01:33,135 --> 00:01:34,720
How about three days from now,

6
00:01:34,886 --> 00:01:36,263
on the 28th at 1 p.m.?

7
00:01:36,513 --> 00:01:37,681
That's fine by me.

8
00:01:38,181 --> 00:01:41,268
Take off everything you're wearing
and put it all in that box.

9
00:01:41,727 --> 00:01:43,520
You can use this blanket.

10
00:01:43,645 --> 00:01:45,230
[Light] Miss Takada, are you all right?

11
00:01:45,939 --> 00:01:48,942
Light, I did exactly what you told me to.

12
00:01:49,026 --> 00:01:51,361
I made survival my first priority and...

13
00:01:51,653 --> 00:01:52,779
And I did it.

14
00:01:53,280 --> 00:01:55,490
Come quickly. Save me.

15
00:01:55,991 --> 00:01:57,034
Kiyomi Takada.

16
00:01:57,200 --> 00:01:58,619
Suicide.

17
00:01:58,744 --> 00:02:01,371
January 26, 2013,

18
00:02:01,538 --> 00:02:02,998
-2:32 p.m.
-[loud heartbeat]

19
00:02:03,165 --> 00:02:06,543
[Light] Burns to death by setting fire
to everything around her,

20
00:02:06,668 --> 00:02:09,004
including everything she wrote on.

21
00:02:09,755 --> 00:02:11,340
It is with great sorrow

22
00:02:11,506 --> 00:02:14,760
that I must announce the passing
of one of our very own colleagues.

23
00:02:15,052 --> 00:02:18,513
The police have identified
one of the bodies found at the scene

24
00:02:18,639 --> 00:02:21,183
as NHN's Ms. Kiyomi Takada.

25
00:02:22,184 --> 00:02:24,144
A two-ton truck and a motorcycle

26
00:02:24,311 --> 00:02:26,730
were also found in the ruins
of the burned-out church.

27
00:02:27,022 --> 00:02:30,192
Investigators suspect
gasoline was used to start the fire.

28
00:02:36,948 --> 00:02:40,702
But what I really want to know is
who's gonna be Kira's next spokesperson?

29
00:02:40,786 --> 00:02:44,424
Kira's message still needs to be spread
and someone's gotta do it.

30
00:02:44,581 --> 00:02:47,334
The death of newscaster Takada
was a horrible tragedy,

31
00:02:47,459 --> 00:02:50,337
but I can't help but think
that if she was that careless,

32
00:02:50,462 --> 00:02:53,006
she couldn't have taken her position
as Kira's spokesperson

33
00:02:53,131 --> 00:02:54,007
that seriously.

34
00:02:54,091 --> 00:02:56,635
It needs to be said:
this is not a woman's job.

35
00:02:56,760 --> 00:02:59,429
Kira, please make me
your new representative.

36
00:02:59,554 --> 00:03:00,431
KIRA'S KINGDOM

37
00:03:00,549 --> 00:03:02,724
No. Give the honor to Sakura TV again!

38
00:03:02,849 --> 00:03:04,017
Disgusting.

39
00:03:04,184 --> 00:03:05,268
Yeah, I know.

40
00:03:05,686 --> 00:03:08,522
I mean, they just announced her death
and already it's started.

41
00:03:08,689 --> 00:03:11,858
Every TV station airing its own segment
on who should replace her.

42
00:03:11,983 --> 00:03:13,485
It's like she never existed.

43
00:03:14,945 --> 00:03:18,031
Last night's judgments
unfolded just as planned.

44
00:03:18,156 --> 00:03:19,574
That means Takada and Mikami

45
00:03:19,658 --> 00:03:21,952
have had no problems
contacting each other.

46
00:03:22,536 --> 00:03:24,413
There's nothing to worry about.

47
00:03:24,621 --> 00:03:25,706
[signal beeping]

48
00:03:26,832 --> 00:03:27,958
[Aizawa] It's Near!

49
00:03:29,918 --> 00:03:31,420
-Hello, L.
-[Light] Yes?

50
00:03:32,379 --> 00:03:33,964
I don't mean to keep bothering you

51
00:03:34,047 --> 00:03:35,716
but with regards to our meeting...

52
00:03:40,345 --> 00:03:44,766
I wanted to confirm that we are still set
for the 28th at 1 p.m. All right?

53
00:03:44,975 --> 00:03:45,934
Yes.

54
00:03:46,476 --> 00:03:48,228
It's just as I predicted.

55
00:03:48,562 --> 00:03:50,480
He's sticking with the original time.

56
00:03:50,731 --> 00:03:52,190
There's no doubt about it.

57
00:03:53,066 --> 00:03:54,109
Very well.

58
00:03:54,317 --> 00:03:56,403
The 28th, the day after tomorrow.

59
00:03:57,821 --> 00:03:58,822
Right.

60
00:04:04,703 --> 00:04:06,705
[Matsuda] So, the day after tomorrow, huh?
Finally.

61
00:04:06,872 --> 00:04:09,207
-Isn't it getting exciting?
-[Ide] Y-- Yeah.

62
00:04:09,332 --> 00:04:11,752
I can't help but wonder
what Near wants to show us.

63
00:04:12,961 --> 00:04:14,796
Matsuda. Ide.

64
00:04:15,005 --> 00:04:16,047
When the day comes,

65
00:04:16,131 --> 00:04:18,258
there's a good chance
we might all be killed.

66
00:04:19,050 --> 00:04:20,886
Don't you understand that?

67
00:04:22,554 --> 00:04:24,055
-[Near] Gevanni.
-[Gevanni] Yes.

68
00:04:24,181 --> 00:04:26,016
[Near] Will you be able
to make it in time?

69
00:04:26,141 --> 00:04:27,976
Yes, I'll be there for sure.

70
00:04:30,854 --> 00:04:32,105
Commander Rester.

71
00:04:32,481 --> 00:04:33,523
Lidner.

72
00:04:33,940 --> 00:04:34,941
Gevanni.

73
00:04:35,484 --> 00:04:37,652
Let's put our best into this, shall we?

74
00:04:50,957 --> 00:04:54,437
JANUARY 28, 2013

75
00:05:04,930 --> 00:05:07,015
[Near] Good morning, everyone.

76
00:05:08,934 --> 00:05:09,893
[Matsuda] Good morning.

77
00:05:11,812 --> 00:05:14,397
First of all, in regard to Misa Amane,

78
00:05:14,606 --> 00:05:16,149
we've already set her free.

79
00:05:16,525 --> 00:05:18,151
You may call her to confirm it.

80
00:05:18,360 --> 00:05:20,028
[beeping]

81
00:05:21,738 --> 00:05:22,948
[Misa] I don't know what's going on,

82
00:05:23,031 --> 00:05:25,450
but this must be some sort of
compensation or something.

83
00:05:25,534 --> 00:05:28,203
They totally put me up
in the penthouse suite at the Teito Hotel.

84
00:05:28,370 --> 00:05:29,538
Can you believe it?

85
00:05:29,663 --> 00:05:31,289
Now this is more like it! [giggles]

86
00:05:31,832 --> 00:05:33,959
I understand. All right, Misa.

87
00:05:34,584 --> 00:05:36,211
Please, stay there
for a little while longer

88
00:05:36,294 --> 00:05:37,420
until I call you.

89
00:05:37,712 --> 00:05:39,005
[Misa] Okay!

90
00:05:40,799 --> 00:05:43,176
All right, Near.
I need you to connect me with Mogi.

91
00:05:43,385 --> 00:05:45,095
We have the notebook
locked away here.

92
00:05:45,178 --> 00:05:47,013
And in order to open the safe
it's kept in,

93
00:05:47,097 --> 00:05:49,641
we'll need the PIN number
from each member of the team.

94
00:05:49,808 --> 00:05:52,561
[Near] Understood.
I'll connect you to him immediately.

95
00:05:54,938 --> 00:05:55,981
This is Mogi.

96
00:05:56,147 --> 00:05:59,568
The number is 62-324.

97
00:05:59,860 --> 00:06:01,778
[keys beeping]

98
00:06:03,280 --> 00:06:05,240
All that's left is my number.

99
00:06:07,450 --> 00:06:08,869
[keys beeping]

100
00:06:14,499 --> 00:06:16,126
The killer notebook…

101
00:06:17,711 --> 00:06:19,004
"How to use it…

102
00:06:19,546 --> 00:06:23,300
The human whose name is
written in this notebook shall die.

103
00:06:23,383 --> 00:06:24,885
This note will not take effect

104
00:06:24,968 --> 00:06:29,639
unless the writer has the person's face
in their mind when writing their name.

105
00:06:29,764 --> 00:06:32,893
Therefore, people sharing
the same name will not be affected.

106
00:06:32,976 --> 00:06:34,352
If the cause of death is written

107
00:06:34,603 --> 00:06:36,730
within 40 seconds of writing
the person's name,

108
00:06:36,897 --> 00:06:37,898
it will happen.

109
00:06:38,106 --> 00:06:40,108
If the cause of death
is not specified,

110
00:06:40,191 --> 00:06:42,068
the person will simply die
of a heart attack.

111
00:06:42,152 --> 00:06:44,154
After writing the cause of death,

112
00:06:44,237 --> 00:06:47,949
details of the death should be written
in the next six minutes and 40 seconds."

113
00:06:52,871 --> 00:06:54,581
Near, it's me.

114
00:06:54,706 --> 00:06:56,458
We've discussed it
and it's been decided

115
00:06:56,541 --> 00:06:58,001
that I'll be the one
to carry the notebook.

116
00:06:58,293 --> 00:07:01,338
L, are you sure it's all right with you
if Mr. Aizawa carries it?

117
00:07:01,504 --> 00:07:02,589
Be honest.

118
00:07:02,881 --> 00:07:03,965
Of course.

119
00:07:04,132 --> 00:07:07,218
I chose Aizawa for the job
because we knew you'd prefer that.

120
00:07:07,469 --> 00:07:08,929
I have no problems with it.

121
00:07:09,721 --> 00:07:11,264
[Near] I appreciate it. Thank you.

122
00:07:12,057 --> 00:07:13,642
Well then, we'll see you shortly.

123
00:07:30,158 --> 00:07:32,494
Looks like this is the end.

124
00:07:32,661 --> 00:07:35,288
No, more like the beginning.

125
00:07:36,539 --> 00:07:39,084
The perfect world of Kira.

126
00:07:42,170 --> 00:07:44,631
And those who know
of the notebook’s existence...

127
00:07:45,382 --> 00:07:48,593
all of them... will die!

128
00:07:55,725 --> 00:07:56,685
[car door opens]

129
00:07:57,102 --> 00:07:58,979
There's no mistake, Near is inside.

130
00:07:59,145 --> 00:08:00,355
I checked it out.

131
00:08:01,481 --> 00:08:03,191
All right. Let's do this.

132
00:09:46,127 --> 00:09:48,588
[exhaust fan squeaking]

133
00:10:03,812 --> 00:10:07,315
Near, you're far inferior to L.

134
00:10:07,732 --> 00:10:11,236
You have no right
to be wearing a mask of L.

135
00:10:11,986 --> 00:10:14,656
It's them. Those four are the SPK.

136
00:10:14,948 --> 00:10:16,950
And the one wearing the mask is Near.

137
00:10:17,492 --> 00:10:20,411
[grumbles] Hang on. Am I the only one
who sees something wrong?

138
00:10:20,662 --> 00:10:22,997
He can go around
accusing people of being Kira,

139
00:10:23,123 --> 00:10:24,791
but the fact that he is wearing the mask

140
00:10:24,874 --> 00:10:27,502
says he's only trying to protect himself,
not anyone else.

141
00:10:29,129 --> 00:10:30,547
[Near] It's just a precaution.

142
00:10:30,922 --> 00:10:33,216
There is a good possibility
that Kira has already seen

143
00:10:33,299 --> 00:10:35,802
the faces of everyone in this warehouse,
except for mine.

144
00:10:36,928 --> 00:10:39,931
In fact, he may be writing down your names
as we speak.

145
00:10:40,515 --> 00:10:42,267
So, I'd like to wait for one hour.

146
00:10:42,517 --> 00:10:44,144
No, make it 30 minutes.

147
00:10:44,227 --> 00:10:45,687
That should give us
more than enough time

148
00:10:45,770 --> 00:10:48,106
to see if anyone is being controlled
before they die.

149
00:10:48,481 --> 00:10:50,066
Huh? What?

150
00:10:50,191 --> 00:10:52,110
You're gonna wait and see if we die?

151
00:10:52,402 --> 00:10:55,780
No, it's not impossible
that Light really is Kira.

152
00:10:56,114 --> 00:10:59,117
Especially since the rest of us
are of no use to him anymore.

153
00:11:00,910 --> 00:11:02,537
[ticking]

154
00:11:05,206 --> 00:11:07,417
[exhaust fan squeaking]

155
00:11:37,447 --> 00:11:40,366
This is all just a front
to buy some time, isn't it?

156
00:11:40,617 --> 00:11:42,702
I never thought it would be this hard

157
00:11:42,827 --> 00:11:45,496
to keep myself from laughing out loud.

158
00:11:45,914 --> 00:11:47,832
Near must be waiting for him to come.

159
00:11:47,999 --> 00:11:50,293
It's all just as I predicted.

160
00:11:53,588 --> 00:11:55,131
[squeaking]

161
00:11:55,506 --> 00:11:57,800
[Matsuda] Near! It's already been
over 30 minutes.

162
00:11:57,884 --> 00:12:00,553
-Nothing's happened yet.
-[Light] Of course not.

163
00:12:00,637 --> 00:12:02,889
That's because Kira is not here with us.

164
00:12:04,474 --> 00:12:05,516
Very well.

165
00:12:05,600 --> 00:12:06,935
Everyone seems to be safe.

166
00:12:07,936 --> 00:12:09,604
I'll remove my mask now.

167
00:12:31,084 --> 00:12:33,086
You're quiet, Near. What's wrong?

168
00:12:34,295 --> 00:12:36,130
Are you still waiting for something?

169
00:12:37,632 --> 00:12:38,716
[Near] Waiting.

170
00:12:38,925 --> 00:12:40,802
That's an excellent choice of words.

171
00:12:41,010 --> 00:12:42,637
Yes, I am waiting.

172
00:12:43,012 --> 00:12:45,848
For the arrival of the one who will
solve everything, once and for all.

173
00:12:46,808 --> 00:12:48,559
Someone else is supposed
to clear this up?

174
00:12:49,102 --> 00:12:50,520
[Near] He'll be here soon.

175
00:12:50,687 --> 00:12:52,230
It's only a matter of time.

176
00:12:52,772 --> 00:12:54,649
There's only one entrance
to this building.

177
00:12:54,983 --> 00:12:56,567
And the only way to look inside

178
00:12:56,734 --> 00:12:58,361
is by opening that door.

179
00:12:58,653 --> 00:13:01,030
That means
he will either through that door,

180
00:13:01,155 --> 00:13:03,783
or at the very least open it
and peek through.

181
00:13:03,992 --> 00:13:06,202
And just who is this person anyway?

182
00:13:06,452 --> 00:13:08,955
X-Kira, the one
who's currently using the notebook

183
00:13:09,080 --> 00:13:10,915
and killing people on Kira's behalf.

184
00:13:11,207 --> 00:13:13,710
He's bound to come here
and bring the notebook with him,

185
00:13:13,876 --> 00:13:16,963
and then he'll see me
and write down my real name.

186
00:13:17,463 --> 00:13:19,882
Or rather, he'll write down
the names of everyone here

187
00:13:19,966 --> 00:13:21,301
who knows about the notebook

188
00:13:21,509 --> 00:13:22,719
and kill them.

189
00:13:22,969 --> 00:13:23,886
[all gasping]

190
00:13:24,971 --> 00:13:25,930
[Matsuda] What?

191
00:13:26,222 --> 00:13:27,724
What are you saying?

192
00:13:27,932 --> 00:13:29,017
This isn't making any sense.

193
00:13:29,142 --> 00:13:30,518
What are you trying to tell us, Near?

194
00:13:30,601 --> 00:13:32,770
That some other guy
is gonna drop by with the notebook,

195
00:13:32,854 --> 00:13:34,397
poke his head in and kill us all?

196
00:13:34,480 --> 00:13:36,566
And you want us to sit back
and let it happen?

197
00:13:37,275 --> 00:13:38,568
[Near] Yes, that's correct.

198
00:13:38,651 --> 00:13:40,194
Now, listen carefully.

199
00:13:40,361 --> 00:13:42,655
If someone comes in to the warehouse
through that door,

200
00:13:42,780 --> 00:13:44,532
just let him in without resisting.

201
00:13:45,074 --> 00:13:46,534
If the door opens slightly,

202
00:13:46,659 --> 00:13:48,745
simply act as if you don't notice
anyone there.

203
00:13:49,162 --> 00:13:51,372
But-- But that's just crazy!

204
00:13:53,333 --> 00:13:54,542
[Near] He's already here.

205
00:13:54,709 --> 00:13:56,544
-[squeaking becomes louder]
-[all gasping]

206
00:14:12,101 --> 00:14:13,195
LIGHT YAGAMI

207
00:14:13,353 --> 00:14:14,270
[Mikami] God!

208
00:14:24,697 --> 00:14:27,450
[Mikami] Delete. Delete. Delete...

209
00:14:27,867 --> 00:14:30,411
-Delete. Delete. Delete. Delete.
-[rat squeaking]

210
00:14:30,578 --> 00:14:35,041
Delete. Delete. Delete.
Delete. Delete. Delete!

211
00:14:35,625 --> 00:14:37,543
Delete. Delete. Delete...

212
00:14:39,837 --> 00:14:40,963
Hold it! Don't do anything!

213
00:14:41,089 --> 00:14:43,049
Everything is fine. You won't die.

214
00:14:43,591 --> 00:14:45,009
[Light] How can you be so sure, Near?

215
00:14:45,093 --> 00:14:47,929
-[Mikami] Delete. Delete. Delete...
-Because I modified the notebook.

216
00:14:48,096 --> 00:14:49,055
[gasping]

217
00:14:49,138 --> 00:14:50,932
[Near] We took repossession
of the notebook

218
00:14:51,015 --> 00:14:52,683
-and replaced the pages.
-[Mikami] Delete....

219
00:14:52,767 --> 00:14:55,103
[Near] The person behind the door
has been doing the killings for Kira.

220
00:14:55,269 --> 00:14:58,314
He has also been using
exactly one page every day.

221
00:14:58,648 --> 00:15:01,818
Based on that, I was able to replace
the page he'd use today,

222
00:15:01,943 --> 00:15:03,945
as well as all subsequent pages,

223
00:15:04,112 --> 00:15:05,655
so that no one else would die.

224
00:15:05,780 --> 00:15:08,157
[Mikami] Delete. Delete. Delete.
Delete. Delete.

225
00:15:08,825 --> 00:15:09,700
Delete!

226
00:15:10,118 --> 00:15:16,624
[yells] Delete!

227
00:15:32,723 --> 00:15:34,434
[sighs]

228
00:15:35,268 --> 00:15:37,603
[Near] On the other side of that door
is X-Kira.

229
00:15:37,854 --> 00:15:39,897
My guess is, in roughly 40 seconds

230
00:15:40,314 --> 00:15:42,400
he'll look inside to see if we're dead.

231
00:15:42,608 --> 00:15:45,027
That's when we'll restrain him
and seize the notebook.

232
00:15:45,736 --> 00:15:47,613
Whoever's name is not written down,

233
00:15:47,697 --> 00:15:49,323
must be Kira.

234
00:15:51,033 --> 00:15:52,285
[Aizawa] It's true.

235
00:15:52,452 --> 00:15:55,746
Kira would be the only one
that guy wouldn't try to kill.

236
00:15:56,539 --> 00:15:57,623
But still...

237
00:16:00,084 --> 00:16:01,586
[stifles laugh]

238
00:16:11,220 --> 00:16:13,764
[Light] I knew it! I knew it! I knew it!

239
00:16:20,271 --> 00:16:23,232
I knew all along
you had tampered with the notebook.

240
00:16:23,399 --> 00:16:26,486
Near, you've been completely defeated!

241
00:16:28,029 --> 00:16:32,200
The notebook you altered was nothing more
than a forgery I had Mikami prepare.

242
00:16:32,492 --> 00:16:33,576
On the other hand,

243
00:16:33,701 --> 00:16:35,536
the one Mikami's writing their names in,

244
00:16:35,703 --> 00:16:39,582
is the real notebook,
which had been kept hidden until now.

245
00:16:40,249 --> 00:16:44,670
[laughing crazily]

246
00:16:47,465 --> 00:16:50,676
I had Mikami
create a fake notebook for himself.

247
00:16:50,760 --> 00:16:53,763
He also sent Takada several pages
from the real one.

248
00:16:53,846 --> 00:16:56,474
So, in fact, it was Takada, not Mikami,

249
00:16:56,557 --> 00:16:57,975
who was doing the killings.

250
00:16:58,518 --> 00:16:59,435
As for Mikami,

251
00:16:59,560 --> 00:17:02,313
I had him write names in public
several times,

252
00:17:02,438 --> 00:17:04,023
using the fake notebook.

253
00:17:04,232 --> 00:17:07,026
That way he would be noticed
by anyone who was following him.

254
00:17:07,276 --> 00:17:09,403
But Takada was the one behind the deaths.

255
00:17:09,529 --> 00:17:12,782
Mikami simply sent the names and faces
by cell phone.

256
00:17:12,865 --> 00:17:15,618
This little performance was
how I made the SPK believe

257
00:17:15,701 --> 00:17:18,037
that the Notebook Mikami used
was the real one.

258
00:17:18,329 --> 00:17:22,208
Mikami's daily behavior is so methodical
it's almost obsessive.

259
00:17:22,792 --> 00:17:26,170
He always fills exactly one page
with names every day.

260
00:17:26,295 --> 00:17:27,255
And Near,

261
00:17:27,338 --> 00:17:28,798
you noticed this little habit

262
00:17:28,923 --> 00:17:31,384
and thought you could use it
to tamper with the notebook.

263
00:17:31,509 --> 00:17:32,468
All you had to do

264
00:17:32,718 --> 00:17:35,888
was count ahead to the page
he'd use on the day of this meeting.

265
00:17:35,972 --> 00:17:39,350
Then you replaced all the pages
from that day onwards.

266
00:17:39,642 --> 00:17:42,395
You'd be confident that you
could prevent anyone from dying.

267
00:17:42,853 --> 00:17:44,689
That was your big plan.

268
00:17:44,772 --> 00:17:48,109
That's why you couldn't change
the date and time of our meeting.

269
00:17:48,442 --> 00:17:50,945
But I was one step ahead of you, Near.

270
00:17:51,237 --> 00:17:54,156
I always knew you were going to try
and alter the Death Note.

271
00:17:54,323 --> 00:17:57,743
That's why I had Mikami
check the notebook every day

272
00:17:57,827 --> 00:17:59,120
MATSUMOTO

273
00:17:59,296 --> 00:18:00,546
for signs of tampering.

274
00:18:01,706 --> 00:18:02,873
I've confirmed it.

275
00:18:03,291 --> 00:18:04,292
[gasps]

276
00:18:07,712 --> 00:18:09,213
TO: KIYOMI TAKADA
I'M DYING TO SEE YOU

277
00:18:09,630 --> 00:18:13,009
I knew I'd won this game
as soon as I got that message.

278
00:18:13,551 --> 00:18:15,845
Mikami brought a different notebook today,

279
00:18:16,012 --> 00:18:17,013
the real one,

280
00:18:17,138 --> 00:18:19,599
which had been kept hidden until now.

281
00:18:23,561 --> 00:18:24,812
But you know, Near,

282
00:18:25,146 --> 00:18:28,316
you did have a chance to win,
if only you'd taken it.

283
00:18:28,441 --> 00:18:30,151
You were just too naive.

284
00:18:30,985 --> 00:18:33,279
You're nothing compared to L.

285
00:18:33,487 --> 00:18:36,198
L would have considered the possibility
of a fake notebook

286
00:18:36,365 --> 00:18:37,742
from the very beginning

287
00:18:37,867 --> 00:18:39,410
And he would have tested it.

288
00:18:39,744 --> 00:18:42,538
You had the chance
but you squandered it.

289
00:18:42,663 --> 00:18:43,956
I've gotta say...

290
00:18:44,248 --> 00:18:46,292
I'm so disappointed in you.

291
00:18:46,751 --> 00:18:48,336
This victory was no fun.

292
00:18:48,461 --> 00:18:51,505
You tried too hard
to win in a noble way.

293
00:18:51,797 --> 00:18:53,007
Well, that's fine.

294
00:18:53,090 --> 00:18:55,885
Everyone here dies today,
thanks to you.

295
00:18:56,010 --> 00:19:00,890
And as for me,
I, Kira, will have my perfect victory.

296
00:19:16,614 --> 00:19:17,907
You there, outside.

297
00:19:18,115 --> 00:19:19,116
Huh?

298
00:19:20,159 --> 00:19:22,161
Have you finished
writing down the names in the notebook?

299
00:19:23,829 --> 00:19:24,830
God!

300
00:19:26,082 --> 00:19:27,792
[Mikami] Yes, I've written them.

301
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:28,876
[all grunt]

302
00:19:31,712 --> 00:19:33,756
[stifles laughter]

303
00:19:33,881 --> 00:19:35,675
No, I can't laugh yet.

304
00:19:35,758 --> 00:19:37,093
I've gotta hold it in.

305
00:19:38,010 --> 00:19:41,972
They're all gonna die 40 seconds
after he wrote down their names.

306
00:19:42,181 --> 00:19:43,641
Thirty-five seconds...

307
00:19:43,724 --> 00:19:45,851
I'll claim my victory then!

308
00:19:46,227 --> 00:19:47,978
[Near] Don't you think it's rather odd?

309
00:19:48,229 --> 00:19:49,105
Huh?

310
00:19:49,438 --> 00:19:52,358
Why would he answer you
so quickly, calmly and honestly,

311
00:19:52,441 --> 00:19:55,403
when you asked him
if he had written down our names yet?

312
00:19:55,528 --> 00:19:57,321
[Light] Who knows? Maybe he's just honest.

313
00:19:57,530 --> 00:19:58,781
Or confident that he'll succeed,

314
00:19:58,864 --> 00:20:01,784
or perhaps he's seen
through your brilliant plan.

315
00:20:01,867 --> 00:20:04,370
[Matsuda] Huh? In that case,
we're in big trouble.

316
00:20:06,205 --> 00:20:07,665
Teru Mikami.

317
00:20:08,290 --> 00:20:09,709
If it's not too much trouble for you,

318
00:20:09,834 --> 00:20:11,836
won't you please come in
and join us.

319
00:20:13,671 --> 00:20:15,172
I already know that you're the one

320
00:20:15,256 --> 00:20:17,675
who's been judging
and executing people for Kira.

321
00:20:17,842 --> 00:20:19,635
If you've already written down our names

322
00:20:19,760 --> 00:20:21,512
then there shouldn't be anything
to be afraid of,

323
00:20:21,721 --> 00:20:22,930
you can come right on in.

324
00:20:26,100 --> 00:20:27,601
Teru Mikami, is it?

325
00:20:27,685 --> 00:20:29,979
He's correct.
There's no reason to hide from us.

326
00:20:30,062 --> 00:20:31,230
-You can come in.
-[men gasp]

327
00:20:32,064 --> 00:20:33,065
God!

328
00:20:54,628 --> 00:20:56,964
You've done well, Mikami.

329
00:20:57,923 --> 00:21:00,968
How many seconds has it been
since you wrote down the first name?

330
00:21:11,479 --> 00:21:12,396
Thirty seconds.

331
00:21:13,022 --> 00:21:15,357
31... 32...

332
00:21:16,066 --> 00:21:18,152
33… 34…

333
00:21:18,944 --> 00:21:20,863
35… 36…

334
00:21:21,280 --> 00:21:22,281
37...

335
00:21:22,573 --> 00:21:23,574
38!

336
00:21:23,783 --> 00:21:24,658
39!

337
00:21:25,659 --> 00:21:27,828
Well, Near, looks like I win.

338
00:21:27,995 --> 00:21:29,663
[Mikami] Forty!

339
00:21:29,789 --> 00:21:36,712
TO BE CONTINUED

340
00:21:41,759 --> 00:21:44,512
[theme music plays]
